      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HI JESSIE (6) has a strong record this trip with 10 wins and nine placings from 30 starts. Hit the frame latest (17.13) when third at this track in a NG. Looks suited and should go close. BYE BYE ROBYN (2) is a good beginner but will need a quick break. Latest effort finished 3rd over 300m at this track beaten 3 lengths (17.37) behind Bugatti Step in a Grade 4/5 on March 26. Rates a key chance on best figures. SNAKE AND LADDER (8) is a quick dog who thrives over the short dashes. Was too tough when scoring last time over 300m at this track in a NG (16.59). Solid record here at the distance winning 13 races. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Likely to be in the finish. WESTERN LIES (1) must be included in main hopes on latest effort.",
